<h1 id="sing-example-tutorial">SING example tutorial</h1>
<p>Liangkang Wang 12/06/2021</p>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
<p>SING method is used in extracting joint non-gaussian components from different datasets when wiping off gaussian noise. This is a tutorial example supporting the paper <strong>Simultaneous Non-Gaussian Component Analysis (SING) for Data Integration in Neuroimaging Benjamin Risk, Irina Gaynanova</strong> <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2005.00597v1">https://arxiv.org/abs/2005.00597v1</a></p>
<p>The function codes are saved in <code>jngcaFunctions.R</code> and <code>generate_data.R</code>. The data processing is saved in <code>My example.R</code> while the figures of outcome are saved in My example2.R`.</p>
